nerator.getInstance(\\\"McEliecePKCS\\\", provider)).isNotNull();\\n            assertThat(provider.getService(\\\"Cipher\\\", \\\"McEliecePKCS\\\")).isNotNull();\\n        } finally {\\n            Security.removeProvider(BouncyCastlePQCProvider.PROVIDER_NAME);\\n            if (previousProvider != null) {\\n                Security.addProvider(previousProvider);\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1780854770773}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcprov-jdk15on:1.48/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-07T17-53-22-139140Z.log:624:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_eUEWhz1PDn5IMZaw7Qb27jAD|fc_0bc7e5e3d710be75016a25aff26d64819495a52aa50cd2fdba\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_bouncycastle.bcprov_jdk15on;\\n\\nimport org.bouncycastle.pqc.jcajce.provider.BouncyCastlePQCProvider;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport java.security.KeyPairGenerator;\\nimport java.security.Provider;\\nimport java.security.Security;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class BouncyCastlePQCProviderTest {\\n    @Test\\n    public void loadsPostQuantumAlgorithmMappings() throws Exception {\\n        Provider previousProvider = Security.getProvider(BouncyCastlePQCProvider.PROVIDER_NAME);\\n        if (previousProvider != null) {\\n            Security.removeProvider(BouncyCastlePQCProvider.PROVIDER_NAME);\\n        }\\n\\n        try {\\n            BouncyCastlePQCProvider provider = new BouncyCastlePQCProvider();\\n            Security.addProvider(provider);\\n\\n            assertThat(provider.getName()).isEqualTo(BouncyCastlePQCProvider.PROVIDER_NAME);\\n            assertThat(provider.getClass().getClassLoader()).isNotNull();\\n            assertThat(provider.hasAlgorithm(\\\"KeyFactory\\\", \\\"Rainbow\\\")).isTrue();\\n            assertThat(provider.hasAlgorithm(\\\"KeyPairGenerator\\\", \\\"Rainbow\\\")).isTrue();\\n            assertThat(provider.hasAlgorithm(\\\"KeyPairGenerator\\\", \\\"McEliecePKCS\\\")).isTrue();\\n            assertThat(provider.hasAlgorithm(\\\"Cipher\\\", \\\"McEliecePKCS\\\")).isTrue();\\n\\n            assertThat(KeyPairGenerator.getInstance(\\\"Rainbow\\\", provider)).isNotNull();\\n            assertThat(KeyPairGenerator.getInstance(\\\"McEliecePKCS\\\", provider)).isNotNull();\\n            assertThat(provider.getService(\\\"Cipher\\\", \\\"McEliecePKCS\\\")).isNotNull();\\n        } finally {\\n            Security.removeProvider(BouncyCastlePQCProvider.PROVIDER_NAME);\\n            if (previousProvider != null) {\\n                Security.addProvider(previousProvider);\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1780854770773}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcprov-jdk15on:1.48/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-07T17-53-22-139140Z.log:649:      public void createsX509StreamParserThroughProviderClassLoader() throws Exception {\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcprov-jdk15on:1.48/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-07T17-53-22-139140Z.log:662:      public void createsX509StreamParserThroughClassForNameFallback() throws Exception {\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcprov-jdk15on:1.48/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-07T17-53-22-139140Z.log:682:              super(\"X509UtilTestProvider\", 1.0, \"Provider for X509Util dynamic access coverage\");\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcprov-jdk15on:1.48/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-07T17-53-22-139140Z.log:704:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_wX